# Z Autonomy Rules

- AI may assist with linting, formatting, analysis, docs generation, build/test verification, and PR drafting.
- AI must not autonomously deploy, change DNS/domains, modify billing/payment systems, merge to production, activate APIs, or make legal/surveillance decisions without explicit human approval.
- Human operators retain final authority for all critical decisions.
- When uncertain, stop and request human confirmation.
